{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7966: App crashes when using router-view, transition, suspense and teleport",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:24:46.188633+00:00",
  "text": "App crashes when using router-view, transition, suspense and teleport\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.2.47\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/vue-router-suspense-transition-teleport-bug-e47p0j?file=%252Fsrc%252FApp.vue\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Click C a few times, notice app is fine\r\n2. Click B\r\n3. Now click C again, app will crash\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nApp should not crash\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nApp crashes with `Uncaught (in promise) TypeError: node is null`\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\nI initially thought this issue was a problem with PrimeVue and raised an issue [there](https://github.com/primefaces/primevue/issues/3805), but after narrowing it down further it seems more like a core vue problem.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: transition",
    "scope: suspense",
    "scope: teleport",
    "has PR",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
